{"id":1639,"date":"2024-08-16T21:17:15","date_gmt":"2024-08-16T21:17:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1639"},"modified":"2024-08-16T21:18:08","modified_gmt":"2024-08-16T21:18:08","slug":"mission-003","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/missions\/mission-003\/","title":{"rendered":"Mission #003: A Minor Scrap"},"content":{"rendered":"<table class=\"table grey left\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">Mission #003: A Minor Scrap<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Start Location<\/th>\n<td>Antisis City, Black Emboar HQ &#8211; goon on upper floor near staircase<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Unlock Requirements<\/th>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Completed main story missions up until Antisis City<\/li>\n<li>Completed <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/missions\/mission-061\/\">#061: The Black Emboar<\/a> (Crater Town)<\/li>\n<li>Completed <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/missions\/mission-073\/\">#073: The Terror Granbull<\/a> (Fallshore City Mission HQ)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Objectives<\/th>\n<td>Participate in a fight against two Black Ferrothorn Goons in the streets of Antisis City<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Reward<\/th>\n<td><u>Item<\/u>: <strong>Power Bracer<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>A member of the Black Emboar in Antisis City wants you to conquer some street turf from their rivals, the Black Ferrothorn, and he\u2019ll give you a Power Bracer if you manage to do it.<\/p>\n<h2>Starting the Mission<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/01-pokemon-unbound-the-black-emboar-hq-in-antisis-city.jpg\" alt=\"The Black Emboar HQ in Antisis City \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>The Black Emboar HQ in Antisis City<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>You\u2019ll first need to have completed <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/missions\/mission-061\/\"><strong>#061: The Black Emboar<\/strong><\/a> in Crater Town. At the end of that mission you defeat James, the leader of the Black Emboar gang. He not only renames the gang in your honor (the Black <em>[Player Name]<\/em>), but he moves the whole operation to Antisis City and starts a turf war with its ruling crew, the Black Ferrothorn.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll also need to have assisted the policeman in Fallshore City Mission HQ with his task to hunt down the Terror Granbull in and near Route 10.<\/p>\n<p>If you\u2019ve done all that, go to the Black Emboar HQ next to the Poke Mart in Antisis City, and head upstairs.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/02-pokemon-unbound-a-tall-order-but-worth-it.jpg\" alt=\"A tall order, but worth it \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>A tall order, but worth it<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Speak to the goon nearest the staircase and he\u2019ll give you the mission.<\/p>\n<p>He\u2019ll tell you to challenge a couple of Black Ferrothorn gang members near the east bridge, but there\u2019s no need to walk there yourself &#8211; you\u2019ll immediately go there together after you finish talking.<\/p>\n<h2>How to Complete<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/03-pokemon-unbound-the-turf-war-battle-begins.jpg\" alt=\"The turf war battle begins \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>The turf war battle begins<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The first stage of this battle begins with one goon at first, and then when you beat him it turns into a Double Battle with the other goon as well. <\/p>\n<p>They also use the mysterious enhancers the scientist in Antisis City makes on their Pok\u00e9mon.<\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey center even-2col tbl-125img\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-big\">Turf War Battle<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><strong>Black Ferrothorn Rory<\/strong><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Weezing<\/strong><br \/>\n        Poison<br \/>\n        (Lv.48)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/04-pokemon-unbound-weezing.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Muk<\/strong><br \/>\n        Poison<br \/>\n        (Lv.49)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/05-pokemon-unbound-muk.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Ferroseed<\/strong><br \/>\n        Grass\/Steel<br \/>\n        (Lv.47)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/06-pokemon-unbound-ferroseed.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Krokorok<\/strong><br \/>\n        Ground\/Dark<br \/>\n        (Lv.49)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/07-pokemon-unbound-krokorok.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><strong>Black Ferrothorn Rory and Black Ferrorthorn Chad<\/strong><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Weezing<\/strong><br \/>\n        Poison<br \/>\n        (Lv.48)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/04-pokemon-unbound-weezing.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Muk<\/strong><br \/>\n        Poison<br \/>\n        (Lv.49)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/05-pokemon-unbound-muk.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Ferrothorn<\/strong><br \/>\n        Grass\/Steel<br \/>\n        (Lv.47)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/08-pokemon-unbound-ferrothorn.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n        <strong>Krookodile<\/strong><br \/>\n        Ground\/Dark<br \/>\n        (Lv.49)\n      <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/09-pokemon-unbound-krookodile.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/missions\/003\/10-pokemon-unbound-a-grateful-goon.jpg\" alt=\"A grateful goon \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>A grateful goon<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>After you win in both battles, you\u2019ll be taken back to the HQ and given the Power Bracer as your reward.<\/p>\n<p>The Power Bracer reduces a Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s Speed stat in exchange for increasing its Attack EVs every time it gains experience.<\/p>\n<div class=\"callout-box\">All Power items can be upgraded using Star Pieces by Black Belt Kentaro &#8211; he\u2019s west of Antisis City near the entrance to Thundercap Mountain.<\/div>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/missions\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/missions-icon.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/missions-icon.jpg 200w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/missions-icon-150x150.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">All Missions<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":1640,"parent":282,"menu_order":2,"template":